EXT. NEIGHBORHOOD - SUNSET
Fading light. The WEATHER is getting worse around the
neighborhood. There’s a short MONTAGE of the town battening
down the hatches to prepare for a storm. The montage ends at
the Mormon Church Building...
INT. CHURCH, PEORIA WARD - SUNSET
...where the Mission President ELDER KENNEDY (50, male), is
leveling a crooked PAINTING of Joseph Smith. We see him move
about the building completing his daily tasks:
- Kennedy scrubs a BAPTISM TUB.
- Kennedy wears an apron, washing dishes in the kitchen.
- Kennedy cleans the keys of a PIPE ORGAN with a Q-Tip.
- Kennedy organizes a series of paperclips by color, an
apparent OCD starting to show.
His diligence forms a picture of a man who is a stickler for
details.
INT. CHURCH, GYM - SUNSET
Kennedy strides through the church gym with purpose, heading
to his next task.
He SLIPS on a WET SPOT and falls hard.
No one was around to see. That’s a relief to him.
He gathers himself. Gazes at a trail of WET FOOTPRINTS.
INT. CHURCH, BATHROOM - SUNSET
Kennedy grabs a MOP and BUCKET.
